msgid "4. Puññābhisandavagga"
msgstr "4. Overflowing Merit"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn55.38:0.3"
msgid "38. Vassasutta"
msgstr "38. Rain"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.396"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: mahāsamuddaṃ → mahāsamuddaṃ sāgaraṃ (bj) | mahāsamuddasāgaraṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.38:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, uparipabbate thullaphusitake deve vassante taṃ "
"udakaṃ yathāninnaṃ pavattamānaṃ pabbatakandarapadarasākhā paripūreti, "
"pabbatakandarapadarasākhā paripūrā kusobbhe paripūrenti, kusobbhā paripūrā "
"mahāsobbhe paripūrenti, mahāsobbhā paripūrā kunnadiyo paripūrenti, kunnadiyo "
"paripūrā mahānadiyo paripūrenti, mahānadiyo paripūrā mahāsamuddaṃ "
"paripūrenti;"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, suppose it rains heavily on a mountain top, and the water flows "
"downhill to fill the hollows, crevices, and creeks. As they become full, "
"they fill up the pools. The pools fill up the lakes, the lakes fill up the "
"streams, and the streams fill up the rivers. And as the rivers become full, "
"they fill up the ocean."

msgctxt "sn55.38:1.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa yo ca buddhe aveccappasādo, yo ca "
"dhamme aveccappasādo, yo ca saṃghe aveccappasādo, yāni ca ariyakantāni "
"sīlāni—"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha, "
"the teaching, and the Saṅgha, and the ethics loved by the noble ones."

msgctxt "sn55.38:1.3"
msgid "ime dhammā sandamānā pāraṃ gantvā āsavānaṃ khayāya saṃvattantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"These things flow onwards; and, after crossing to the far shore, they lead "
"to the ending of defilements.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.38:1.4"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
